    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_cūdyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cūdyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>cūdt</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>codun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>cudt</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>пошатываться</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>totter</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>fæcūdyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пошатнуться</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>stagger</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>wyrdyǵy ænæ cūdgæ... bīræ fæwajʒæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(лошадь) долго будет бежать по спуску не шатаясь</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(the horse) will run downhill for a long time without staggering</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>70</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>æ sabitæ kæwgæ, cotgæ bajzadæncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>его дети остались плачущие, шатающиеся</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>his children were left crying, tottering</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            165</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Сопоставление <bibl><author>Вс. Миллера</author></bibl> с
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čud-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>čod-</w>
                        <gloss><q>побуждать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>подгонять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>торопить</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 151</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>) трудно принять из-за рас- хождения
                    значений. Скорее %icūd%i- — перебой из *%itūd%i- (ср. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæfsyn"/> || <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsyn"/>
                    ‘греться’); в этом случае ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>tud-</w>
                        <gloss><q>толкать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>тыкать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>ttund-</w>
                        <gloss><q>отшатываться</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>отклоняться (от правды)</q></gloss></mentioned>’? (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Leumann"
                        /><biblScope>273%l235%l</biblScope></bibl>). В осетинском удержалось
                    медиальное значение (ср. ‘шатать’ — ‘шататься’); для развития значения ср.
                    образованное от того же корня <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>totter</w>
                        <gloss><q>шататься</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en"><bibl><author>Ws. Miller's</author></bibl> comparison with
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>čud-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>čod-</w>
                        <gloss><q>induce</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>urge on</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>hurry</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 151</biblScope></bibl>;
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                            /><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>) is hard to accept because of meaning
                    differences. The root %icūd%i- is rather the change from *%itūd%i- (cf. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_cæfsyn"/> || <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæfsyn"
                    /> ‘warm onesefl’); in this case cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>tud-</w>
                        <gloss><q>push</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>poke</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>ttund-</w>
                        <gloss><q>recoil from</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>stray (from the truth)</q></gloss></mentioned>’? (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Leumann"
                        /><biblScope>273%l235%l</biblScope></bibl>). In Ossetic middle voice meaning
                    is kept (cf. ‘rock’ — ‘totter’); for the development of the meaning cf.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/>
                        <w>totter</w></mentioned> which is derived from the same root.</etym>
            </entry>
